INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$General Security Concepts$sp1$, 2, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A database administrator can read and modify customer records, but the application logs every change with a timestamp and the user ID so the action cannot later be denied. Which security principle does this logging primarily provide?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Confidentiality"},{"id":"b","text":"Availability"},{"id":"c","text":"Non-repudiation"},{"id":"d","text":"Least privilege"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["c"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Non-repudiation ensures a party cannot credibly deny having performed an action. Tamper-evident logs that bind an action to an authenticated identity provide non-repudiation. Confidentiality and availability are separate CIA goals, and least privilege is an access-control practice.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/12/r1/final","label":"NIST SP 800-12 Rev. 1 — Information security concepts"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, true, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A database administrator can read and modify customer records, but the application logs every change with a timestamp and the user ID so the action cannot later be denied. Which security principle does this logging primarily provide?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$General Security Concepts$sp1$, 2, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$In the AAA framework, a user successfully enters a valid username and password and is then granted access only to the resources their role permits. Which two AAA functions are illustrated, in order?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Authorization, then accounting"},{"id":"b","text":"Authentication, then authorization"},{"id":"c","text":"Accounting, then authentication"},{"id":"d","text":"Authorization, then authentication"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Verifying the credentials proves identity (authentication). Determining which resources the proven identity may access is authorization. Accounting is the later recording of what the user actually did.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$In the AAA framework, a user successfully enters a valid username and password and is then granted access only to the resources their role permits. Which two AAA functions are illustrated, in order?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$General Security Concepts$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A network architect is designing access so that no device or user is trusted by default and every request is verified regardless of network location. Which model is being applied?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Defense in depth using only perimeter firewalls"},{"id":"b","text":"Zero trust architecture"},{"id":"c","text":"Implicit trust within the corporate LAN"},{"id":"d","text":"Air-gapped segmentation"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Zero trust eliminates implicit trust based on network location and continuously verifies every access request. Perimeter-only and implicit-LAN-trust models assume internal traffic is safe, which zero trust rejects.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/207/final","label":"NIST SP 800-207 — Zero Trust Architecture"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A network architect is designing access so that no device or user is trusted by default and every request is verified regardless of network location. Which model is being applied?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$General Security Concepts$sp1$, 3, $sp1$MULTI$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$Select ALL elements that are part of a zero trust control plane / policy-driven access decision as described by NIST SP 800-207.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"A policy engine that evaluates trust before granting access"},{"id":"b","text":"A policy administrator that establishes or terminates the connection"},{"id":"c","text":"A flat network where any host can reach any other host once on the LAN"},{"id":"d","text":"Continuous evaluation of subject and device state"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a","b","d"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$NIST SP 800-207 defines a policy engine (decision), a policy administrator (enforces/establishes the session), and continuous evaluation of subject/asset state. A flat, openly reachable LAN is the opposite of zero trust.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/207/final","label":"NIST SP 800-207 — Zero Trust Architecture"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, true, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$Select ALL elements that are part of a zero trust control plane / policy-driven access decision as described by NIST SP 800-207.$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$General Security Concepts$sp1$, 2, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A company encrypts a message with the recipient's public key so that only the recipient can read it. Which property of public key infrastructure is being used?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Asymmetric encryption for confidentiality"},{"id":"b","text":"Symmetric key exchange for non-repudiation"},{"id":"c","text":"Hashing for integrity"},{"id":"d","text":"Steganography for obfuscation"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Encrypting with the recipient's public key means only the matching private key can decrypt, providing confidentiality through asymmetric (public-key) cryptography. Hashing provides integrity, not confidentiality, and steganography hides existence rather than encrypting content.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/175/b/r1/final","label":"NIST SP 800-175B Rev. 1 — Guideline for using cryptographic standards"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A company encrypts a message with the recipient's public key so that only the recipient can read it. Which property of public key infrastructure is being used?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$General Security Concepts$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A developer wants to prove that a downloaded firmware image has not been altered and genuinely came from the vendor. Which combination best achieves this?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"A symmetric key shared with all customers"},{"id":"b","text":"A digital signature created with the vendor's private key and verified with its public key"},{"id":"c","text":"Base64 encoding of the firmware"},{"id":"d","text":"A salted password hash of the file name"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$A digital signature is a hash of the image encrypted with the signer's private key; verifying it with the vendor's public key proves both integrity and authenticity (origin). Encoding and password hashing do not provide origin assurance.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/175/b/r1/final","label":"NIST SP 800-175B Rev. 1 — Guideline for using cryptographic standards"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A developer wants to prove that a downloaded firmware image has not been altered and genuinely came from the vendor. Which combination best achieves this?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$General Security Concepts$sp1$, 2, $sp1$TRUE_FALSE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A change management process that requires approvals, testing, and a documented rollback plan before modifying production systems is primarily a security control, not just an IT operations practice.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"True"},{"id":"b","text":"False"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$True. Controlled change management reduces the risk of misconfiguration, unapproved changes, and outages, all of which have security and availability impact, so it is a recognized security control area in the Security+ objectives.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A change management process that requires approvals, testing, and a documented rollback plan before modifying production systems is primarily a security control, not just an IT operations practice.$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$General Security Concepts$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$An organization deploys honeypots and fake credentials to lure and detect attackers. Which category of security control does this represent?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Deterrent and deception technology"},{"id":"b","text":"Corrective control"},{"id":"c","text":"Compensating physical control"},{"id":"d","text":"Directive policy control"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Honeypots, honeytokens, and decoy credentials are deception and disruption technologies that detect and mislead attackers. They are not corrective (which restore after an event) or purely directive (policy guidance).$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$An organization deploys honeypots and fake credentials to lure and detect attackers. Which category of security control does this represent?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Threats, Vulnerabilities, and Mitigations$sp1$, 2, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$An employee receives an email appearing to be from the CEO urgently requesting a wire transfer. The email targets a specific finance manager by name and title. Which attack is this?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Generic phishing"},{"id":"b","text":"Spear phishing / business email compromise"},{"id":"c","text":"Smishing"},{"id":"d","text":"Tailgating"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$A targeted email aimed at a specific individual using known details (and impersonating an executive for fraudulent payment) is spear phishing, commonly the basis of business email compromise. Generic phishing is untargeted; smishing uses SMS; tailgating is physical.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, true, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$An employee receives an email appearing to be from the CEO urgently requesting a wire transfer. The email targets a specific finance manager by name and title. Which attack is this?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Threats, Vulnerabilities, and Mitigations$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A nation-state group conducts a long-term, stealthy intrusion to exfiltrate intellectual property over many months while avoiding detection. This threat actor is best classified as which?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Unskilled attacker (script kiddie)"},{"id":"b","text":"Hacktivist"},{"id":"c","text":"Advanced persistent threat (APT)"},{"id":"d","text":"Insider error"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["c"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$A well-resourced, stealthy, long-dwell actor (often nation-state sponsored) pursuing strategic data over time is an advanced persistent threat. Unskilled attackers lack sophistication, hacktivists pursue ideology publicly, and an insider error is unintentional.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A nation-state group conducts a long-term, stealthy intrusion to exfiltrate intellectual property over many months while avoiding detection. This threat actor is best classified as which?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Threats, Vulnerabilities, and Mitigations$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A web application concatenates user input directly into a SQL query. An attacker submits ' OR '1'='1 into the login field and bypasses authentication. Which mitigation most directly prevents this?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Enforcing TLS 1.3 on the site"},{"id":"b","text":"Using parameterized queries / prepared statements with input validation"},{"id":"c","text":"Increasing the password complexity policy"},{"id":"d","text":"Enabling full-disk encryption on the database server"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$SQL injection is prevented by parameterized queries (prepared statements) that separate code from data, plus server-side input validation. TLS protects data in transit, and disk encryption or password policy do not stop injection.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A web application concatenates user input directly into a SQL query. An attacker submits ' OR '1'='1 into the login field and bypasses authentication. Which mitigation most directly prevents this?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Threats, Vulnerabilities, and Mitigations$sp1$, 2, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$Malware encrypts a victim's files and demands payment for the decryption key. Which malware type is this?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Rootkit"},{"id":"b","text":"Ransomware"},{"id":"c","text":"Logic bomb"},{"id":"d","text":"Keylogger"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Ransomware encrypts data (or systems) and extorts payment for restoration. A rootkit hides presence, a logic bomb triggers on a condition, and a keylogger captures keystrokes.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$Malware encrypts a victim's files and demands payment for the decryption key. Which malware type is this?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Threats, Vulnerabilities, and Mitigations$sp1$, 3, $sp1$MULTI$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$Select ALL indicators that would suggest a system is compromised by malware rather than experiencing a benign performance issue.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Outbound connections to known malicious command-and-control IP addresses"},{"id":"b","text":"Unexpected new scheduled tasks and unknown persistence registry keys"},{"id":"c","text":"A planned, announced maintenance reboot during the change window"},{"id":"d","text":"Account lockouts and logins from impossible-travel locations"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a","b","d"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$C2 callouts, unexplained persistence mechanisms, and anomalous authentication (impossible travel, lockouts) are classic indicators of compromise. A scheduled, announced maintenance reboot is expected operational activity.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/61/r2/final","label":"NIST SP 800-61 Rev. 2 — Computer security incident handling guide"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$Select ALL indicators that would suggest a system is compromised by malware rather than experiencing a benign performance issue.$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Threats, Vulnerabilities, and Mitigations$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$An attacker exploits a software flaw for which no patch yet exists and the vendor is unaware. What is this called?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"A zero-day vulnerability"},{"id":"b","text":"A misconfiguration"},{"id":"c","text":"An end-of-life vulnerability"},{"id":"d","text":"A race condition that is always benign"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$A zero-day is a vulnerability unknown to the vendor with no available patch, leaving defenders zero days to prepare. End-of-life issues stem from unsupported software, and a misconfiguration is an avoidable setup error.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$An attacker exploits a software flaw for which no patch yet exists and the vendor is unaware. What is this called?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Threats, Vulnerabilities, and Mitigations$sp1$, 2, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$An attacker places an infected USB drive in a company parking lot hoping an employee plugs it in. Which social engineering technique relies on the victim's curiosity in this way?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Baiting"},{"id":"b","text":"Vishing"},{"id":"c","text":"Pretexting only"},{"id":"d","text":"Watering hole attack"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Baiting leaves enticing media (such as USB drives) for victims to use, delivering malware. Vishing is voice phishing, pretexting fabricates a scenario, and a watering hole compromises a site the target visits.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, true, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$An attacker places an infected USB drive in a company parking lot hoping an employee plugs it in. Which social engineering technique relies on the victim's curiosity in this way?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Threats, Vulnerabilities, and Mitigations$sp1$, 4, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A penetration tester captures traffic and replays a previously valid authentication token to gain access. Which attack class is this, and which mitigation is most appropriate?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Replay attack — mitigate with nonces/timestamps and short-lived tokens"},{"id":"b","text":"Brute force — mitigate with longer passwords only"},{"id":"c","text":"Phishing — mitigate with user training only"},{"id":"d","text":"Buffer overflow — mitigate with ASLR"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Reusing a captured valid token is a replay attack. Per-session nonces, timestamps, and short-lived/one-time tokens defeat replay. Password length, training, or ASLR address unrelated attack classes.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/63/b/final","label":"NIST SP 800-63B — Digital identity / authentication"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A penetration tester captures traffic and replays a previously valid authentication token to gain access. Which attack class is this, and which mitigation is most appropriate?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Threats, Vulnerabilities, and Mitigations$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A vulnerability scan reports a CVSS base score of 9.8 for an internet-facing server with a public exploit available. According to risk-based prioritization, how should this be treated?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Defer until the next annual maintenance window"},{"id":"b","text":"Prioritize for immediate remediation due to high severity, exposure, and exploitability"},{"id":"c","text":"Ignore because scanners produce only false positives"},{"id":"d","text":"Accept the risk without documentation"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$A critical CVSS score on an internet-facing asset with a known public exploit is high likelihood and high impact, so it should be remediated urgently. Deferring, ignoring, or silently accepting such risk is not defensible.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/40/r4/final","label":"NIST SP 800-40 Rev. 4 — Guide to enterprise patch management planning"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A vulnerability scan reports a CVSS base score of 9.8 for an internet-facing server with a public exploit available. According to risk-based prioritization, how should this be treated?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Threats, Vulnerabilities, and Mitigations$sp1$, 2, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$An attacker overwhelms a web service with traffic from thousands of compromised hosts so legitimate users cannot reach it. Which attack is described?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Distributed denial-of-service (DDoS)"},{"id":"b","text":"On-path (man-in-the-middle)"},{"id":"c","text":"Privilege escalation"},{"id":"d","text":"Cross-site scripting"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Flooding a service from many compromised hosts (a botnet) to exhaust resources is a distributed denial-of-service attack. The other options describe interception, gaining higher rights, and injecting scripts into pages.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$An attacker overwhelms a web service with traffic from thousands of compromised hosts so legitimate users cannot reach it. Which attack is described?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Threats, Vulnerabilities, and Mitigations$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A web form reflects unsanitized user input back into the page, allowing an attacker to run script in another user's browser. Which vulnerability is this and the primary fix?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Cross-site scripting (XSS) — output encoding and input validation"},{"id":"b","text":"SQL injection — full-disk encryption"},{"id":"c","text":"Directory traversal — stronger Wi-Fi passwords"},{"id":"d","text":"CSRF — disabling TLS"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Reflecting unsanitized input that executes in a victim's browser is cross-site scripting. Context-aware output encoding plus input validation (and a content security policy) mitigate it. The other fixes do not address XSS.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A web form reflects unsanitized user input back into the page, allowing an attacker to run script in another user's browser. Which vulnerability is this and the primary fix?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Threats, Vulnerabilities, and Mitigations$sp1$, 3, $sp1$TRUE_FALSE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$Network segmentation reduces the impact of a compromised host by limiting an attacker's lateral movement to other systems.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"True"},{"id":"b","text":"False"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$True. Segmentation and microsegmentation contain a breach to a smaller zone, restricting lateral movement and limiting blast radius, which is a standard mitigation technique.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$Network segmentation reduces the impact of a compromised host by limiting an attacker's lateral movement to other systems.$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Threats, Vulnerabilities, and Mitigations$sp1$, 4, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A trusted developer with legitimate access deliberately inserts a logic bomb that deletes data 30 days after their account is disabled. Which threat does this best illustrate?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Malicious insider threat"},{"id":"b","text":"Unintentional misconfiguration"},{"id":"c","text":"Supply chain compromise of a third party"},{"id":"d","text":"Shadow IT"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$An authorized person abusing legitimate access to plant destructive code is a malicious insider threat. It is intentional (not misconfiguration), originates internally (not third-party supply chain), and is not unsanctioned tooling (shadow IT).$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A trusted developer with legitimate access deliberately inserts a logic bomb that deletes data 30 days after their account is disabled. Which threat does this best illustrate?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Threats, Vulnerabilities, and Mitigations$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$Two processes use a shared resource without proper locking, and an attacker exploits the gap between a check and the subsequent use. Which vulnerability class is this?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Time-of-check to time-of-use (race condition)"},{"id":"b","text":"Buffer overflow"},{"id":"c","text":"Insecure deserialization"},{"id":"d","text":"Open redirect"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Exploiting the window between validating a condition and acting on it is a time-of-check/time-of-use race condition. Buffer overflow corrupts memory, deserialization issues execute crafted objects, and open redirect abuses URL handling.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$Two processes use a shared resource without proper locking, and an attacker exploits the gap between a check and the subsequent use. Which vulnerability class is this?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Architecture$sp1$, 2, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$In the cloud shared responsibility model for Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS), which task is the customer's responsibility?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Securing the physical data center"},{"id":"b","text":"Patching the guest operating system and applications they deploy"},{"id":"c","text":"Maintaining the hypervisor"},{"id":"d","text":"Replacing failed physical disks"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Under IaaS the provider secures the physical facility, hardware, and hypervisor, while the customer is responsible for the guest OS, applications, and data they deploy. The other options are provider responsibilities.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, true, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$In the cloud shared responsibility model for Infrastructure as a Service (IaaS), which task is the customer's responsibility?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Architecture$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$An architect places public-facing web servers in a screened subnet (DMZ) separated from the internal network by firewalls. What is the primary security benefit?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"It eliminates the need to patch the web servers"},{"id":"b","text":"It limits direct exposure of the internal network if a public server is compromised"},{"id":"c","text":"It encrypts all traffic automatically"},{"id":"d","text":"It provides multi-factor authentication"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$A screened subnet isolates internet-facing systems so that a compromise there does not give direct access to internal resources. It does not remove patching needs, nor inherently provide encryption or MFA.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$An architect places public-facing web servers in a screened subnet (DMZ) separated from the internal network by firewalls. What is the primary security benefit?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Architecture$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A company wants to ensure that if one data center fails, operations continue at another site with minimal interruption. Which architectural concept is this?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"High availability through redundancy and failover"},{"id":"b","text":"Data minimization"},{"id":"c","text":"Obfuscation"},{"id":"d","text":"Least privilege"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Redundant sites with failover provide high availability and resilience against a single point of failure. Data minimization, obfuscation, and least privilege address data exposure and access, not site resilience.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/34/r1/final","label":"NIST SP 800-34 Rev. 1 — Contingency planning guide"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A company wants to ensure that if one data center fails, operations continue at another site with minimal interruption. Which architectural concept is this?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Architecture$sp1$, 3, $sp1$MULTI$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$Select ALL techniques that protect data confidentiality at rest or in use rather than only in transit.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Full-disk encryption on laptops"},{"id":"b","text":"Database column-level encryption / tokenization"},{"id":"c","text":"TLS for HTTPS sessions"},{"id":"d","text":"Hardware security module (HSM) protecting keys used by an application"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a","b","d"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Full-disk encryption and column-level encryption/tokenization protect data at rest, and an HSM protects keys used while data is processed. TLS protects data in transit, not at rest.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/57/pt1/r5/final","label":"NIST SP 800-57 Part 1 Rev. 5 — Recommendation for key management"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$Select ALL techniques that protect data confidentiality at rest or in use rather than only in transit.$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Architecture$sp1$, 2, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A firewall rule set ends with an explicit "deny all" after specific allow rules. Which secure design principle does this implement?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Implicit allow"},{"id":"b","text":"Default deny / least functionality"},{"id":"c","text":"Open by default"},{"id":"d","text":"Security through obscurity"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Ending with deny-all enforces a default-deny posture so only explicitly permitted traffic passes, reducing attack surface (least functionality). Implicit/open-by-default would allow unlisted traffic, and obscurity is unrelated.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A firewall rule set ends with an explicit "deny all" after specific allow rules. Which secure design principle does this implement?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Architecture$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$An organization adopts a Secure Access Service Edge (SASE) solution. What does this primarily converge?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Networking (SD-WAN) and security services delivered from the cloud"},{"id":"b","text":"Only on-premises antivirus signatures"},{"id":"c","text":"Physical badge readers and CCTV"},{"id":"d","text":"Database backup schedules"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$SASE converges WAN networking (SD-WAN) with cloud-delivered security services such as secure web gateway, CASB, and zero trust network access, enabling consistent policy for distributed users. It is not about physical access or backups.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/207/final","label":"NIST SP 800-207 — Zero Trust Architecture"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$An organization adopts a Secure Access Service Edge (SASE) solution. What does this primarily converge?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Architecture$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A company stores backups using the 3-2-1 strategy. Which arrangement satisfies it?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Three copies, on two different media types, with one copy stored off-site"},{"id":"b","text":"Three copies all on the same server"},{"id":"c","text":"One copy on a single cloud bucket only"},{"id":"d","text":"Two copies on the same disk with one extra file name"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$The 3-2-1 rule means at least three copies of data, on at least two different media types, with at least one copy kept off-site, improving resilience against device failure and site loss.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/34/r1/final","label":"NIST SP 800-34 Rev. 1 — Contingency planning guide"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A company stores backups using the 3-2-1 strategy. Which arrangement satisfies it?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Architecture$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A microservices application is deployed in containers. Which control best limits the blast radius if one container is compromised?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Running every container as root for convenience"},{"id":"b","text":"Network policies / segmentation between services and least-privilege service accounts"},{"id":"c","text":"Disabling all logging"},{"id":"d","text":"Sharing a single secret across all services"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Segmenting service-to-service traffic and granting each workload only the privileges it needs constrains lateral movement after a container compromise. Running as root, disabling logging, and sharing secrets all increase risk.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/207/final","label":"NIST SP 800-207 — Zero Trust Architecture"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A microservices application is deployed in containers. Which control best limits the blast radius if one container is compromised?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Architecture$sp1$, 2, $sp1$TRUE_FALSE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A virtual private network (VPN) using IPsec or TLS primarily protects the confidentiality and integrity of data while it traverses an untrusted network.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"True"},{"id":"b","text":"False"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$True. VPN tunnels encrypt and integrity-protect traffic between endpoints across untrusted networks such as the internet, defending against eavesdropping and tampering in transit.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/175/b/r1/final","label":"NIST SP 800-175B Rev. 1 — Guideline for using cryptographic standards"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A virtual private network (VPN) using IPsec or TLS primarily protects the confidentiality and integrity of data while it traverses an untrusted network.$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Architecture$sp1$, 4, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$An architect must protect an industrial control system (ICS/SCADA) that cannot be patched frequently and must not be exposed to the internet. Which approach is most appropriate?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Connect it directly to the corporate Wi-Fi for convenience"},{"id":"b","text":"Isolate it on a segmented OT network with strict allow-listed access and monitoring"},{"id":"c","text":"Expose it via a public IP with a default password"},{"id":"d","text":"Disable all monitoring to reduce overhead"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Fragile OT/ICS systems are best protected by network isolation/segmentation, tightly controlled (allow-listed) access, and monitoring, compensating for limited patching. Direct internet or Wi-Fi exposure dramatically increases risk.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$An architect must protect an industrial control system (ICS/SCADA) that cannot be patched frequently and must not be exposed to the internet. Which approach is most appropriate?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Architecture$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$An application masks all but the last four digits of stored credit card numbers when displayed to support staff. Which data protection technique is this?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Data masking"},{"id":"b","text":"Full-disk encryption"},{"id":"c","text":"Key escrow"},{"id":"d","text":"Load balancing"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Showing only partial values (last four digits) is data masking, which limits exposure of sensitive data to those who do not need the full value. It is distinct from encryption, key escrow, or load balancing.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/122/final","label":"NIST SP 800-122 — Guide to protecting the confidentiality of PII"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$An application masks all but the last four digits of stored credit card numbers when displayed to support staff. Which data protection technique is this?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Architecture$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$To reduce the chance that a single administrator can unilaterally cause harm, a design requires two different administrators to approve a critical production change. Which principle is applied?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Separation of duties"},{"id":"b","text":"Single sign-on"},{"id":"c","text":"Federation"},{"id":"d","text":"Defense in depth at the perimeter only"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Requiring two people to complete or approve a sensitive action enforces separation of duties (and dual control), reducing fraud and error risk. SSO and federation concern authentication, not approval segregation.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$To reduce the chance that a single administrator can unilaterally cause harm, a design requires two different administrators to approve a critical production change. Which principle is applied?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Operations$sp1$, 2, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A system administrator removes unused services, closes unnecessary ports, and disables default accounts on a new server before deployment. This process is best described as which?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"System hardening"},{"id":"b","text":"Penetration testing"},{"id":"c","text":"Threat hunting"},{"id":"d","text":"Tabletop exercise"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Reducing attack surface by removing unneeded services, ports, and default accounts is system hardening (least functionality). Penetration testing simulates attacks, threat hunting proactively searches for adversaries, and a tabletop is a discussion-based exercise.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/128/final","label":"NIST SP 800-128 — Security-focused configuration management"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, true, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A system administrator removes unused services, closes unnecessary ports, and disables default accounts on a new server before deployment. This process is best described as which?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Operations$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A SIEM correlates logs from firewalls, endpoints, and servers and alerts on a pattern matching a known attack. What is the primary value the SIEM provides here?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"It encrypts all log data automatically at the source"},{"id":"b","text":"Centralized aggregation and correlation for faster detection and investigation"},{"id":"c","text":"It eliminates the need for any human analysts"},{"id":"d","text":"It patches vulnerable systems automatically"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$A SIEM centralizes and correlates events from many sources to detect patterns and speed investigation. It does not inherently encrypt sources, replace analysts, or patch systems.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/92/final","label":"NIST SP 800-92 — Guide to computer security log management"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A SIEM correlates logs from firewalls, endpoints, and servers and alerts on a pattern matching a known attack. What is the primary value the SIEM provides here?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Operations$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$According to NIST SP 800-61, what is the correct ordering of the incident response life cycle phases?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Containment → Preparation → Detection → Recovery"},{"id":"b","text":"Preparation → Detection and Analysis → Containment, Eradication, and Recovery → Post-incident Activity"},{"id":"c","text":"Detection → Recovery → Preparation → Lessons learned"},{"id":"d","text":"Eradication → Preparation → Detection → Containment"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$NIST SP 800-61 defines the cycle as Preparation; Detection and Analysis; Containment, Eradication, and Recovery; and Post-incident Activity (lessons learned). The other sequences are out of order.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/61/r2/final","label":"NIST SP 800-61 Rev. 2 — Computer security incident handling guide"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$According to NIST SP 800-61, what is the correct ordering of the incident response life cycle phases?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Operations$sp1$, 4, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$During a confirmed ransomware incident, the on-call analyst's immediate priority after detection should be which action?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Pay the ransom immediately"},{"id":"b","text":"Contain the incident by isolating affected systems to stop spread"},{"id":"c","text":"Reimage every machine company-wide before any analysis"},{"id":"d","text":"Delete all logs to free disk space"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$After detection, containment (isolating affected hosts/segments) limits spread and preserves the environment for analysis. Paying ransom is discouraged and risky, mass reimaging destroys evidence prematurely, and deleting logs hampers investigation.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/61/r2/final","label":"NIST SP 800-61 Rev. 2 — Computer security incident handling guide"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$During a confirmed ransomware incident, the on-call analyst's immediate priority after detection should be which action?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Operations$sp1$, 3, $sp1$MULTI$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$Select ALL practices that correctly preserve digital evidence during a forensic investigation.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Create a bit-for-bit forensic image and work from a verified copy"},{"id":"b","text":"Maintain a documented chain of custody"},{"id":"c","text":"Calculate and record cryptographic hashes to prove integrity"},{"id":"d","text":"Analyze directly on the live original drive without imaging"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a","b","c"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Forensic best practice is to image evidence, hash it to prove integrity, and maintain chain of custody. Working directly on the original drive risks altering evidence and is improper.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/86/final","label":"NIST SP 800-86 — Integrating forensic techniques into incident response"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, true, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$Select ALL practices that correctly preserve digital evidence during a forensic investigation.$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Operations$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A company implements role-based access control (RBAC). A new accountant is hired. How are permissions assigned most efficiently and securely?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Copy permissions from a random existing user"},{"id":"b","text":"Assign the user to the Accountant role, which carries the predefined least-privilege permissions"},{"id":"c","text":"Grant domain administrator so nothing is blocked"},{"id":"d","text":"Give no access and let the user request each file individually forever"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$RBAC assigns users to roles whose permissions reflect job needs (least privilege), making provisioning consistent and auditable. Copying arbitrary accounts causes privilege creep, and granting admin violates least privilege.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A company implements role-based access control (RBAC). A new accountant is hired. How are permissions assigned most efficiently and securely?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Operations$sp1$, 2, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A bank requires a password plus a one-time code from an authenticator app to log in. Which authentication concept is this?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Single-factor authentication"},{"id":"b","text":"Multi-factor authentication using something you know and something you have"},{"id":"c","text":"Federation"},{"id":"d","text":"Accounting"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Combining a password (something you know) with an authenticator-generated code (something you have) is multi-factor authentication, which is stronger than any single factor. Federation and accounting are unrelated concepts.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/63/b/final","label":"NIST SP 800-63B — Digital identity / authentication"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A bank requires a password plus a one-time code from an authenticator app to log in. Which authentication concept is this?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Operations$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A vulnerability management program rescans assets after patching to confirm the flaw is no longer present. What is this step called?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Validation / remediation verification"},{"id":"b","text":"Reconnaissance"},{"id":"c","text":"Exploitation"},{"id":"d","text":"Social engineering"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Re-scanning after remediation to confirm the vulnerability is fixed is validation (remediation verification), closing the loop in the vulnerability management cycle. The other terms describe attacker activities.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/40/r4/final","label":"NIST SP 800-40 Rev. 4 — Guide to enterprise patch management planning"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A vulnerability management program rescans assets after patching to confirm the flaw is no longer present. What is this step called?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Operations$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A security team writes a SOAR playbook that automatically isolates a host and opens a ticket when an EDR alert fires. What is the main benefit of this automation?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"It guarantees zero false positives"},{"id":"b","text":"Faster, consistent response and reduced mean time to respond"},{"id":"c","text":"It removes the need for any logging"},{"id":"d","text":"It makes encryption unnecessary"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Security orchestration, automation, and response (SOAR) executes predefined playbooks to respond quickly and consistently, lowering mean time to respond and analyst workload. It does not eliminate false positives or other controls.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A security team writes a SOAR playbook that automatically isolates a host and opens a ticket when an EDR alert fires. What is the main benefit of this automation?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Operations$sp1$, 2, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A company configures all workstations to retrieve security patches automatically from a managed update service after testing. Which operational practice is this?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Patch management"},{"id":"b","text":"Penetration testing"},{"id":"c","text":"Data classification"},{"id":"d","text":"Key rotation"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Systematically testing and deploying vendor updates is patch management, which reduces exposure to known vulnerabilities. The other options address attack simulation, data labeling, and cryptographic key lifecycle.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/40/r4/final","label":"NIST SP 800-40 Rev. 4 — Guide to enterprise patch management planning"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A company configures all workstations to retrieve security patches automatically from a managed update service after testing. Which operational practice is this?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Operations$sp1$, 4, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$An EDR product flags a legitimate internal backup tool as malicious and blocks it, disrupting backups. How should this finding be classified and handled?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"True positive — leave it blocked permanently"},{"id":"b","text":"False positive — investigate, then tune/allow-list the legitimate tool"},{"id":"c","text":"False negative — ignore the alert"},{"id":"d","text":"True negative — escalate to law enforcement"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$An alert on benign, legitimate activity is a false positive. The correct handling is to investigate, confirm the tool is authorized, and tune or allow-list it to prevent recurring disruption while keeping detection effective.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/92/final","label":"NIST SP 800-92 — Guide to computer security log management"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$An EDR product flags a legitimate internal backup tool as malicious and blocks it, disrupting backups. How should this finding be classified and handled?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Operations$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$An organization disables an employee's accounts, collects assets, and revokes badge access on their last day. Which IAM process is this?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Provisioning"},{"id":"b","text":"Deprovisioning / offboarding"},{"id":"c","text":"Privilege escalation"},{"id":"d","text":"Federation"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Removing access and recovering assets when someone leaves is deprovisioning (offboarding), essential to prevent orphaned accounts and unauthorized access. Provisioning is the onboarding counterpart.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$An organization disables an employee's accounts, collects assets, and revokes badge access on their last day. Which IAM process is this?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Operations$sp1$, 3, $sp1$TRUE_FALSE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$Time synchronization (for example via NTP) across logging systems is important so that correlated events have accurate, comparable timestamps during an investigation.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"True"},{"id":"b","text":"False"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$True. Without synchronized clocks, event timelines across systems cannot be reliably correlated, undermining detection and forensic reconstruction, so consistent time sources are a logging best practice.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/92/final","label":"NIST SP 800-92 — Guide to computer security log management"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$Time synchronization (for example via NTP) across logging systems is important so that correlated events have accurate, comparable timestamps during an investigation.$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Operations$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A security analyst proactively searches the environment for signs of an undetected intrusion using threat intelligence and hypotheses, rather than waiting for an alert. This activity is called what?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Threat hunting"},{"id":"b","text":"Patch management"},{"id":"c","text":"Backup rotation"},{"id":"d","text":"User awareness training"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Proactively hypothesizing and searching for adversary activity that evaded automated detection is threat hunting. The other options are reactive or preventive operational tasks unrelated to active searching.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A security analyst proactively searches the environment for signs of an undetected intrusion using threat intelligence and hypotheses, rather than waiting for an alert. This activity is called what?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Operations$sp1$, 2, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A company enforces that privileged administrative accounts use a separate credential and are checked out from a privileged access management (PAM) vault with session recording. What risk does this most directly reduce?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Misuse and compromise of high-privilege accounts"},{"id":"b","text":"Physical theft of laptops only"},{"id":"c","text":"DNS cache poisoning"},{"id":"d","text":"Cross-site scripting in web apps"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PAM with separate privileged credentials, just-in-time checkout, and session recording reduces the risk and impact of privileged account misuse or compromise. It does not address physical theft, DNS poisoning, or XSS.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A company enforces that privileged administrative accounts use a separate credential and are checked out from a privileged access management (PAM) vault with session recording. What risk does this most directly reduce?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Operations$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A baseline configuration is defined and systems are continuously checked for unauthorized deviations. Which operational control is this?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Configuration management with drift detection"},{"id":"b","text":"Penetration testing"},{"id":"c","text":"Phishing simulation"},{"id":"d","text":"Data loss prevention"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Establishing secure baselines and monitoring for unauthorized changes (drift) is security-focused configuration management. It differs from offensive testing, awareness simulations, and DLP, which address other risks.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/128/final","label":"NIST SP 800-128 — Security-focused configuration management"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A baseline configuration is defined and systems are continuously checked for unauthorized deviations. Which operational control is this?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Operations$sp1$, 2, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$Before disposing of old hard drives containing sensitive data, the company physically shreds the platters. Which control objective does this satisfy?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Secure media sanitization to prevent data remanence"},{"id":"b","text":"High availability"},{"id":"c","text":"Load balancing"},{"id":"d","text":"Single sign-on"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Physically destroying media ensures sensitive data cannot be recovered (no data remanence), satisfying secure sanitization/disposal requirements. The other options are unrelated to data destruction.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/88/r1/final","label":"NIST SP 800-88 Rev. 1 — Guidelines for media sanitization"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$Before disposing of old hard drives containing sensitive data, the company physically shreds the platters. Which control objective does this satisfy?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Operations$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A new mobile device enrollment policy requires devices to report OS version, encryption status, and jailbreak/root status before being granted access to corporate resources. Which operational control is this?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Device posture / health attestation as a condition of access"},{"id":"b","text":"A penetration test of the app store"},{"id":"c","text":"A risk register entry only"},{"id":"d","text":"A change advisory board meeting"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Evaluating device health (patch level, encryption, integrity) before allowing access enforces device posture/attestation, a key operational control in zero-trust and mobile security. The other options are unrelated governance or testing activities.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/207/final","label":"NIST SP 800-207 — Zero Trust Architecture"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A new mobile device enrollment policy requires devices to report OS version, encryption status, and jailbreak/root status before being granted access to corporate resources. Which operational control is this?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Program Management and Oversight$sp1$, 2, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$An organization identifies a risk, decides the cost of mitigation exceeds the potential loss, documents the decision, and chooses to take no further action. Which risk treatment is this?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Risk transfer"},{"id":"b","text":"Risk acceptance"},{"id":"c","text":"Risk avoidance"},{"id":"d","text":"Risk mitigation"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Knowingly and formally choosing to live with a risk because treatment is not cost-effective is risk acceptance. Transfer shifts it (for example via insurance), avoidance removes the activity, and mitigation reduces it with controls.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/37/r2/final","label":"NIST SP 800-37 Rev. 2 — Risk Management Framework"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, true, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$An organization identifies a risk, decides the cost of mitigation exceeds the potential loss, documents the decision, and chooses to take no further action. Which risk treatment is this?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Program Management and Oversight$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A company purchases cyber insurance to cover potential breach costs. Which risk treatment strategy does this represent?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Risk acceptance"},{"id":"b","text":"Risk transfer"},{"id":"c","text":"Risk avoidance"},{"id":"d","text":"Risk mitigation through hardening"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Shifting the financial impact of a risk to a third party (an insurer) is risk transfer. It does not reduce the likelihood of the event the way mitigation does, nor eliminate the activity (avoidance).$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/37/r2/final","label":"NIST SP 800-37 Rev. 2 — Risk Management Framework"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A company purchases cyber insurance to cover potential breach costs. Which risk treatment strategy does this represent?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Program Management and Oversight$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$In a quantitative risk assessment, an asset is worth $100,000, a fire would destroy 40% of it (exposure factor), and such a fire is expected once every 10 years. What is the annualized loss expectancy (ALE)?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"$40,000"},{"id":"b","text":"$4,000"},{"id":"c","text":"$400,000"},{"id":"d","text":"$10,000"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Single loss expectancy = $100,000 × 0.40 = $40,000. Annualized rate of occurrence = 1/10 = 0.1. ALE = SLE × ARO = $40,000 × 0.1 = $4,000.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/37/r2/final","label":"NIST SP 800-37 Rev. 2 — Risk Management Framework"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$In a quantitative risk assessment, an asset is worth $100,000, a fire would destroy 40% of it (exposure factor), and such a fire is expected once every 10 years. What is the annualized loss expectancy (ALE)?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Program Management and Oversight$sp1$, 3, $sp1$MULTI$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$Select ALL items that are typically defined in an agreement governing a relationship with a third-party service provider.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Service level agreement (SLA) with availability and response targets"},{"id":"b","text":"Right-to-audit clause and security requirements"},{"id":"c","text":"The provider's personal social media passwords"},{"id":"d","text":"Data handling, breach notification, and confidentiality (NDA) terms"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a","b","d"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Third-party agreements commonly include SLAs, right-to-audit and security requirements, and data handling/breach notification/confidentiality terms. A provider's personal social media passwords are never an appropriate contractual element.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/161/r1/final","label":"NIST SP 800-161 Rev. 1 — Cybersecurity supply chain risk management"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$Select ALL items that are typically defined in an agreement governing a relationship with a third-party service provider.$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Program Management and Oversight$sp1$, 2, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$Which document is a non-binding agreement that expresses the intent of two parties to work together before a formal contract is signed?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Memorandum of understanding (MOU)"},{"id":"b","text":"Service level agreement (SLA)"},{"id":"c","text":"Master service agreement (MSA)"},{"id":"d","text":"Business partners agreement (BPA)"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$A memorandum of understanding states a mutual intent to cooperate and is generally non-binding. An SLA defines measurable service levels, an MSA sets overarching contract terms, and a BPA governs a partnership.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$Which document is a non-binding agreement that expresses the intent of two parties to work together before a formal contract is signed?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Program Management and Oversight$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A regulation requires that EU residents' personal data be processed lawfully and that breaches be reported within a strict timeframe. Which compliance driver is this most associated with?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"GDPR (data privacy regulation)"},{"id":"b","text":"A voluntary marketing guideline"},{"id":"c","text":"An internal naming convention"},{"id":"d","text":"A firewall vendor manual"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Lawful processing of EU residents' personal data and mandatory breach notification within tight deadlines are hallmarks of the GDPR, a privacy regulation. The other options are not enforceable compliance obligations.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/122/final","label":"NIST SP 800-122 — Guide to protecting the confidentiality of PII"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A regulation requires that EU residents' personal data be processed lawfully and that breaches be reported within a strict timeframe. Which compliance driver is this most associated with?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Program Management and Oversight$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$An external firm with no operational stake performs an objective evaluation of the organization's controls against a standard and issues a formal opinion. What is this best described as?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"An independent third-party audit / assessment"},{"id":"b","text":"A phishing campaign"},{"id":"c","text":"A penetration test scoped only to Wi-Fi"},{"id":"d","text":"A tabletop exercise run internally"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$An impartial external evaluation of controls against a standard with a formal opinion is an independent third-party audit/assessment, valued for objectivity. The other options are different activities with different goals.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/37/r2/final","label":"NIST SP 800-37 Rev. 2 — Risk Management Framework"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$An external firm with no operational stake performs an objective evaluation of the organization's controls against a standard and issues a formal opinion. What is this best described as?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Program Management and Oversight$sp1$, 2, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A company runs simulated phishing emails and short training modules for staff each quarter. Which program element is this?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Security awareness and training"},{"id":"b","text":"Disaster recovery testing"},{"id":"c","text":"Change advisory board"},{"id":"d","text":"Penetration testing"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Recurring phishing simulations and user education are part of a security awareness and training program that reduces human-factor risk. It is distinct from DR testing, change governance, and offensive testing.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://www.comptia.org/certifications/security","label":"CompTIA — Security+ (SY0-701) exam objectives"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, true, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A company runs simulated phishing emails and short training modules for staff each quarter. Which program element is this?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Program Management and Oversight$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A business impact analysis (BIA) for a critical system sets a recovery time objective (RTO) of 4 hours. What does the RTO specify?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"The maximum acceptable amount of data loss measured in time"},{"id":"b","text":"The maximum tolerable time to restore the system after a disruption"},{"id":"c","text":"The average age of the hardware"},{"id":"d","text":"The encryption key length to use"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$RTO is the maximum tolerable duration to restore a system/process after disruption. The maximum acceptable data loss measured in time is the recovery point objective (RPO), a different BIA metric.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/34/r1/final","label":"NIST SP 800-34 Rev. 1 — Contingency planning guide"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A business impact analysis (BIA) for a critical system sets a recovery time objective (RTO) of 4 hours. What does the RTO specify?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Program Management and Oversight$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$During vendor selection, the security team reviews a supplier's SOC 2 report, security questionnaire, and software bill of materials. Which program activity is this?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"Third-party / supply chain risk assessment (due diligence)"},{"id":"b","text":"Internal salary benchmarking"},{"id":"c","text":"Marketing analysis"},{"id":"d","text":"Help desk ticket triage"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Evaluating a supplier's attestations, questionnaire responses, and SBOM before engagement is supply chain/third-party risk due diligence, reducing risk inherited from vendors. The other options are unrelated business functions.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/161/r1/final","label":"NIST SP 800-161 Rev. 1 — Cybersecurity supply chain risk management"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$During vendor selection, the security team reviews a supplier's SOC 2 report, security questionnaire, and software bill of materials. Which program activity is this?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Program Management and Oversight$sp1$, 2, $sp1$TRUE_FALSE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A data classification policy that labels data as public, internal, confidential, or restricted helps ensure protection controls are applied proportionally to data sensitivity.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"True"},{"id":"b","text":"False"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$True. Classifying data by sensitivity lets the organization apply proportionate handling, storage, and access controls and is a foundational governance practice for managing information risk.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/122/final","label":"NIST SP 800-122 — Guide to protecting the confidentiality of PII"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A data classification policy that labels data as public, internal, confidential, or restricted helps ensure protection controls are applied proportionally to data sensitivity.$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Program Management and Oversight$sp1$, 3, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$An organization adopts a recognized cybersecurity framework to organize its program around functions such as Identify, Protect, Detect, Respond, and Recover. Which framework is described?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"The NIST Cybersecurity Framework"},{"id":"b","text":"A change request form"},{"id":"c","text":"An acceptable use poster"},{"id":"d","text":"A network cabling diagram"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["a"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$The Identify, Protect, Detect, Respond, and Recover (and Govern) functions describe the NIST Cybersecurity Framework, used to structure and mature a security program. The other options are not frameworks.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/37/r2/final","label":"NIST SP 800-37 Rev. 2 — Risk Management Framework"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$An organization adopts a recognized cybersecurity framework to organize its program around functions such as Identify, Protect, Detect, Respond, and Recover. Which framework is described?$sp1$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", domain, difficulty, type, stem, options, correct, explanation, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", version, "createdAt", "updatedAt") SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $sp1$Security Program Management and Oversight$sp1$, 4, $sp1$SINGLE$sp1$::"QType", $sp1$A risk owner accepts a residual risk that exceeds the organization's defined risk appetite without senior leadership approval. Why is this problematic from a governance standpoint?$sp1$, $sp1$[{"id":"a","text":"It improves accountability and oversight"},{"id":"b","text":"Risks beyond the stated appetite require appropriate authority/governance sign-off, so unilateral acceptance undermines oversight"},{"id":"c","text":"Risk appetite has no bearing on acceptance decisions"},{"id":"d","text":"It automatically transfers the risk to a vendor"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$["b"]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$Governance requires that risks exceeding the defined risk appetite/tolerance be escalated for acceptance by an appropriate authority. Unilateral acceptance bypasses oversight and accountability, which is a governance failure; it does not transfer the risk.$sp1$, $sp1$[{"url":"https://csrc.nist.gov/pubs/sp/800/37/r2/final","label":"NIST SP 800-37 Rev. 2 — Risk Management Framework"}]$sp1$::jsonb, $sp1$PUBLISHED$sp1$::"QStatus", $sp1$manual:securityplus-seed$sp1$, false, 1, NOW(), NOW() FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.slug = $sp1$comptia-security-plus-p1$sp1$ AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $sp1$A risk owner accepts a residual risk that exceeds the organization's defined risk appetite without senior leadership approval. Why is this problematic from a governance standpoint?$sp1$);
